# [FLT37-CASEII-II1-REROUTE] The genuine single-root linear-measure Case-II descent

## Why the previous endpoint was vacuous

The FLT37 Case-II II1 leaf was carried as `CaseIIRealIdealDescent37`
(`RealGeneratorBridge.lean`): for each `CaseIIData37` and adjacent root `ő∑ ‚Č† ő∑‚āÄ`, a nonzero ideal
`J` of `ūĚďě K‚Āļ` with `J.map = ūĚĒě(ő∑)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ`.  This is **provably false**:

* `ŌÉ(ūĚĒě(ő∑)) = ūĚĒě(ő∑‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)` (`caseII_map_rootIdeal`), so for an adjacent root the single-quotient
  `ūĚĒě(ő∑)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ` is sent by `ŌÉ` to `ūĚĒě(ő∑‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ ‚Č† ūĚĒě(ő∑)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ`.  A `J ‚äÜ ūĚďě K‚Āļ` would force `ūĚĒě(ő∑)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ` to be
  `ŌÉ`-stable.  So no such `J` exists, and every endpoint resting on `CaseIIRealIdealDescent37` is
  vacuous.

## The honest residual

Washington's ¬ß9.4 descent step
(`caseII_descent_step_of_adjacent_etaZeroSpanSingletons_and_unitPower`,
`SpecificChain.lean`) does **not** require a `ūĚďě K‚Āļ` ideal or `ŌÉ`-fixed generator.  It requires only
that the single-root **anchored quotients** `ūĚĒě(ő∑‚āĀ)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ`, `ūĚĒě(ő∑‚āā)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ` at the two adjacent roots
`ő∑‚āĀ = ő∑‚āÄő∂`, `ő∑‚āā = ő∑‚āÄő∂¬≤` are **principal in `ūĚďě K`** (generated by ratios `a/b` of elements of
`ūĚďě K`, with `a, b` coprime to `ő∂ - 1`).  Equivalently `[ūĚĒě(ő∑‚āĀ)] = [ūĚĒě‚āÄ] = [ūĚĒě(ő∑‚āā)]` in `Cl(ūĚďě K)`.

This is the genuine Washington ¬ß9.1 `B_a` content.  It is the irreducible obstruction: the class
`[ūĚĒě(ő∑)/ūĚĒě‚āÄ]` lies in `Cl‚ĀĽ(ūĚďě K)[37]` (it pairs with its conjugate to land in `Cl‚Āļ[37] = 0`, by
Vandiver / `caseII_sigma_stable_ideal_descends`), which is generally **nonzero** for the irregular
prime `37`.  It is **strictly more honest** than `CaseIIRealIdealDescent37`, which additionally ‚ÄĒ
and
falsely ‚ÄĒ demanded `ūĚďě K‚Āļ`-descent (hence `ŌÉ`-stability).

`CaseIIAdjacentSingleRootQuotientPrincipal37` names exactly this single-root principality.  This
file:

* defines the residual `CaseIIAdjacentSingleRootQuotientPrincipal37` (`def ‚Ä¶ : Prop`, **not** an
  axiom);
* derives the strict `CaseIIData37` descent step from it + Assumption II (the proven
  `WashingtonCaseIIExactQuotientUnitPower37Source`) via the **linear-measure** Washington descent
  `caseII_descent_step_of_adjacent_etaZeroSpanSingletons_and_unitPower`;
* assembles a top-level `FermatLastTheoremFor 37` resting on the residual + Assumption II + the
  user-owned second-order input ‚ÄĒ **with `CaseIIRealIdealDescent37` entirely removed**.

It imports only; it does **not** modify any existing file.

